The first of the three panel data regression techniques used in this paper is referred to as the mean group (MG) estimator developed by Pesaran and Smith (1995). The MG estimation primarily involves the estimation of the slope coefficients for each of the cross-sections, within the panel dataset, using the ordinary least squares (OLS) method and then averaging them across the panel units. This allows for the possible heterogeneity of the slope coefficients across the different cross-sections to overcome the inefficiencies of the FMOLS and the DOLS techniques. The MG estimator can be specified as:13\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
